name: Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Milwaukee Downtown
description:
Located in the heart of the Milwaukee city center, this hotel is 7 minutes’ walk from the Fivserv forum, home of basketball’s Bucks. Free Wi-Fi is offered, and each room includes a fridge.
A flat-screen cable TV is provided in every room at Fairfield Inn & Suites by Marriott Milwaukee Downtown.
A daily continental breakfast is served as well as a convenience store with additional snacks is located on site.
A fitness center is available at this hotel. Launderette facilities are offered, as well as 24-hour reception services. V
Veterans Park with access to Lake Michigan is 1 miles away. General Mitchell International Airport can be reached in 14 minutes’ drive.

name: Cambria Hotel Milwaukee Downtown
description:
Located in Milwaukee, a 19-minute walk from Marquette University, Cambria Hotel Milwaukee Downtown has accommodations with a fitness center, private parking, a shared lounge and a restaurant. This 4-star hotel offers a 24-hour front desk, a concierge service and free WiFi. Guests can have a drink at the bar.
Rooms are complete with a private bathroom, while some rooms at the hotel also have a seating area.
Cambria Hotel Milwaukee Downtown offers an à la carte or American breakfast.
Popular points of interest near the accommodation include Riverside Theater, Pabst Theater and Eisner Museum. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 6.2 miles from Cambria Hotel Milwaukee Downtown.

name: Tru By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown, WI
description:
Featuring 2-star accommodations, Tru By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown, WI is located in Milwaukee, 1.3 miles from Marquette University and 3.5 miles from University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee. Featuring a terrace, the 2-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. Private parking can be arranged at an extra charge.
Guest rooms in the hotel are equipped with a TV. At Tru By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown, WI every room is equipped with bed linen and towels.
An American breakfast is available daily at the accommodation.
Tru By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown, WI can conveniently provide information at the reception to help guests to get around the area.
Popular points of interest near the hotel include Skylight Music Theatre, Eisner Museum and Riverside Theater. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 6.2 miles from Tru By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown, WI.

name: Residence Inn Milwaukee Downtown
description:
Centrally located downtown along the Milwaukee RiverWalk, this elegant hotel is connected to the Shops of Grand Avenue. The all-suite hotel features free Wi-Fi and rooms with city views.
Every suite at Residence Inn Milwaukee Downtown features a seating area with floor-to-ceiling windows and a kitchenette. A 37-inch flat-screen TV and iPod docking station are also featured.
This Milwaukee Residence Inn is located in the historic Marshall Fields building. It offers a 24-hour gym and business center as well as an onsite gift shop.
Guests can enjoy a hot buffet breakfast in the Hearth Room and a social hour with light dining and cocktails offered on select nights. A 24-hour market provides snacks and beverages for guest convenience.
This Residence Inn Downtown is within 10 minutes' walk of the Wisconsin Center and Bradley Center sports arena. Marquette and Discovery World are a 15 minute walk away.

name: The Pfister Hotel
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at The Pfister Hotel! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Offering a full-service spa, salon and Victorian art collection, this 4-star hotel is located in downtown Milwaukee. The property is a 10-minute walk from the Milwaukee Art Museum and provides WiFi to guests.
The guest rooms at The Pfister Hotel feature a flat-screen TV and MP3 docking station. The private bathroom has spa bath amenities, a hairdryer and telephone. Some rooms include views of downtown Milwaukee or Lake Michigan.
Guests can enjoy the Pfister's indoor pool or the well-equipped gym with cardio equipment. Hotel shops and a business center are also available.
Blu, the martini bar located on the hotel's 23rd floor, boast excellent views of the city. The Mason Street Grill serves American cuisine including wood grilled steaks, sandwiches and homemade desserts. Room service is available 24 hours.

name: Hotel Metro, Autograph Collection
description:
Centrally located in downtown Milwaukee, this historic Art Deco inspired hotel is 15 minutes' walk from the Milwaukee Art Museum and Lake Michigan waterfront. Hotel Metro features gourmet dining and a rooftop deck with panoramic city views.
Each modern suite offers a spacious living area with a fully stocked mini-bar. A 42-inch flat-screen TV and free WiFi are both included. Robes and slippers are provided in the deluxe bathrooms.
Hotel Metro's rooftop tikibar "Pufferfish Tiki" features a fireplace, cozy indoor and outdoor seating, as well as unbeatable rooftop views.
Oggie's Kitchen and Bar is open for breakfast, dinner and Happy Hour Monday-Thursday 4PM-7PM & Friday 4PM-6PM.
The Harley Davidson Museum, BMO Harris Bradley Center and the Wisconsin Center are within 1 miles of the Hotel Metro.

userReviews.negative: the parking.  I get that parking is limited in the city so this is going to be difficult to solve.  However, the key card exits of the hotel that were closest to the parking garage were “not working” so we needed to take luggage and small children all the way around the building.  I talked to an employee about the doors, thinking it was our key cards and they informed me that it has been weeks since they have not been working and they don’t know why!!!!   This was extremely frustrating!  Also, parking in the front of property should be 20 minute parking for check-in/out.   The street parking when we arrived was completely full, so there wasn’t a place for us to park to check-in and unload our luggage.  We were not familiar with the area so it was stressful and very time consuming when we needed to be at an event.  We saw the same cars parked in front of the building all day and night.  Finally, we booked on-line 3 double queen suites.   I called the property and asked due to small children and a disabled adult to be close together on the same floor.  I talked with Vanessa and she said that they would do their best.  On September 9th, our check-in day I tried calling 2 times to see about an early check-in and nobody answered!  I went to the property hoping for the best.   I checked in with Vanessa and once again asked for all of the rooms to be on the same floor as close as possible.  She told me that she could do that.  She also told me that it would be at least 45 minutes (approximately 2:00)before any of the rooms would be ready, I told her that would be great!  When that time came she said that only 2 of the rooms were available, the third one would be longer.  I checked in the two rooms and I reminded her that we needed the 3rd room to be on the same floor, she told me no problem.   I checked in with her 2 more times, still not ready.

userReviews.title: Great staff
userReviews.positive:
For me the staff made the place shine (as is actually,  literally,  true). From the friendly, helpful woman who checked us in, to Ricky, the magnificent night manager (if he's not a manager,  he should be), every person i interacted with was pretty great.  Give them all a raise,  but especially,  Ricky. 
Because I broke my face when I was catapulted head first into a concrete wall entering the stairwell to the parking garage by tripping on the stair (more on this later), I was monitoring myself for signs of concussion, so I stayed up and ended up hanging out in the lobby until 3 a.m. During that time I had the pleasure of conversation with Ricky, as well as the opportunity to watch him interact with all kinds of guests,  callers, and situations with skill and courtesy.  And because of him, I plan to come back. 
Also,  the bed  and pillows were super comfy, and the kitchenette wonderful.
userReviews.negative:
Even though the parking garage is not owned / operated by the hotel, many hotel customers use the garage to park,  so I'm going to share.  I went to parking garage from the hotel to grab something from the car. Just as I entered the stairwell to garage, I tripped on an unseen/unusually high step and flung myself into the concrete wall in front of me. I noticed later that there is a sign inside the stairwell warning of the step down, but nothing outside warning of the step up. So, be careful. But, one of the things I learned hanging out in the lobby that you would want to know: the parking lot right next to the parking garage is owned by the hotel and only costs $10 vs the approx $25 we paid to park in the garage. You're welcome. Bonus, no steps, hidden or otherwise. 
There was an issue with our thermostat and the fan blowing out cold air,  which would have sucked if it wasn't, coincidentally, a freakishly warm winter day so we could just turn the fan off altogether and be fine. Also,  I couldn't get (or figure out how to get) hot water when I wanted to take a shower. That was quite possibly an operator error thing, especially considering I had just recently slammed my head into a concrete wall,  but I thought I would mention it as I've been operating showers for 50 years and have never found myself in that situation before. And finally,  the breakfast was underwhelming,  to me. But if you are a fan of microwaved Jimmy Dean breakfast sandwiches and muffins you will enjoy the breakfast,  to each their own.
But I'm still planning to come back,  because I believe that if I had asked, Ricky, would have made me eggs benedict ;-)

description:
Steps away from the scenic RiverWalk, this downtown Milwaukee hotel is 1 miles away from Marquette University and offers a 24-hour fitness center, indoor pool and free WiFi.
Featuring large windows and 9-foot high ceilings, every room at aloft Hotel Milwaukee Downtown includes a 42-inch flat-screen LCD TV, small refrigerator and work station with large desk and ergonomic chair. A small refrigerator and coffee machine are also included.
Guests can enjoy a drink at W XYZ Bar or sip while playing pool at the hotel lounge. A 24-hour snack shop, meeting and event space are all offered at Downtown Milwaukee aloft Hotel.
Fiserv Forum is a 5-minute walk away from the hotel. The Milwaukee Art Museum is a 9-minute drive away.

name: Milwaukee Marriott Downtown
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Milwaukee Marriott Downtown! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Featuring an on-site restaurant , this Milwaukee hotel is 1 miles from the scenic Lakeshore State Park.  Each guest room is equipped with a 36-inch flat-screen TV.
Tea and coffee-making facilities are provided in every room at Milwaukee Marriott Downtown.  The air-conditioned rooms include a spacious work desk.
East Town Kitchen & Bar is located on the property and offers a classic menu, approachable vibe, and one of the best whiskey lists in all of Wisconsin.  An on-site Starbucks café offers coffee daily.
A fitness center and launderette facilities are offered to all guests at Marriott Milwaukee Downtown.  Guests can enjoy valet dry cleaning service or the business center in the lobby.
Miller Park, home of baseball’s Milwaukee Brewers, is 5 miles from this hotel.  The Frontier Airlines Convention Center can be reached in 10 minutes’ walk.

name: Kinn Guesthouse Downtown
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Kinn Guesthouse Downtown! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Kinn Guesthouse Downtown in Milwaukee features 5-star accommodations with a restaurant and a bar. With a shared lounge, the 5-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. The hotel has family rooms.
All rooms come with a flat-screen TV, and some units at the hotel have a city view.
Popular points of interest near Kinn Guesthouse Downtown include Marquette University, Riverside Theater and Pabst Theater. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 6.2 miles from the accommodation.

userReviews.title: Exceptional
userReviews.positive:
I would highly recommend anyone visiting Milwaukee to stay at Kinn Guesthouse.
The location is so central and perfect for exploring by both foot and transport. The bedroom, bathroom and shared spaces were extremely clean, spacious and beautifully decorated. 
Michael was so welcoming and really went above and beyond during our stay - thank you again!
We were a little apprehensive about booking Kinn Guesthouse after reading some of the comments that highlighted issues with checking in and poor WiFi. However from start to finish, this was never an issue. The process they have in place is so seamless and WiFi strength was strong.
After checking out, Rosa was able to store our luggage so we could do some last minute exploring until it was time to leave for our train to Chicago.

userReviews.title: High end amenities, chic furnishings, ample space, and prime location
userReviews.positive:
The quality and the styling of the property far exceeded my expectations.  The kitchen and the common spaces were outfitted with high end appliances (subzero, wolf) and extremely chic styling.  
Internet speed was sufficient for a day of video calls.  
The coffee bar was stocked with a nespresso, french press, a wide selection of teas, as well as dairy and non-dairy (!) milks.  
On the weekend, we were pleasantly surprised by the pastries in the morning, and the wine in the evening.  
In room, loved the Brooklinen washcloths, but wish all the towels had been brooklinen!  
Contactless checkin was super easy, as we arrived pretty late.
userReviews.negative:
Dishes seemed to pile up in the sink regularly because the dish washer was full, no one knew whether the dishes were clean or dirty, and who was responsible for unloading. Most of the house rules were clearly stated, but responsibility/expectations for the dishwasher could be improved.  
The high-tech locks on the room were not intuitive to 'wake up'.  You must cover the entire lock with your hand in order for the buttons to illuminate.

userReviews.title: Amazing stay. Loved everything about it!
userReviews.positive:
I traveled with my teen to Milwaukee to see a concert at the Riverside theater and we were blown away by the guest house, it’s amenities, and how central it was to everything we wanted to do. We parked our van in the pay lot across the street and didn’t get back in it until we checked out. Milwaukee Public Market, dinner, brunch, all of it was right there and a short walk to all. We enjoyed cruising past all of the folks waiting for ride services after the show and we’re in our very cozy beds within minutes. The rooms are beautiful- we loved the very tall ceilings and decor. The rooms were very quiet, as well, and temperature very well regulated. Bathrooms are beautiful and spacious. The only issue we had was that water leaked out of the shower onto the floor- but we just set a towel on the edge of the shower and it solved it. We loved the 11am check out and that we could still
access the building (and restrooms) and our floor until 4pm that day which was helpful when we were still doing some walking around downtown. Such a cool place to stay. Will definitely be back!

name: Hilton Milwaukee City Center
description:
This Milwaukee hotel is connected by an indoor skywalk to the Wisconsin Center convention facility. The hotel offers multiple restaurants, a bar, a full service Starbucks, and a business center.
Hilton Milwaukee City Center features cable TV and a coffee maker in every guest room.
Guests can workout in the on site fitness center. The front desk is available 24-hours a day.
The Milwaukee ChopHouse at the Milwaukee Hilton serves steaks and seafood for dinner each evening. The Miller Time Pub & Lounge is open for lunch and dinner daily. The Monarch Lounge serves drinks and appetizers each evening.

name: Courtyard Milwaukee Downtown
description:
Centrally located in Milwaukee, Courtyard Downtown is across the road from the Grand Avenue Shopping Mall.
Rooms at the Courtyard Milwaukee Downtown include free wired internet connection, a 27” flat-screen TV and a coffee maker. The private bathrooms are equipped with shower.
Guests can enjoy a daily breakfast or dinner at the The Bistro or benefit from the central location and discover the many eateries that surround the property.
Facilities of the hotel include an indoor pool and a well-equipped gym. The Courtyard Milwaukee Downtown hotel is 7 miles from the County Zoo and 1 miles from Milwaukee Art Museum.

name: Hyatt Regency Milwaukee
description:
Connected to the Wisconsin Convention Center, this contemporary hotel is located in downtown Milwaukee and offers an on-site restaurant, 24-hour fitness center and free WiFi.
Every room at Hyatt Regency Milwaukee provides a 32-inch flat-screen cable TV, iPod docking station and refrigerator. Some rooms also offers views of the city and river. Room service is available.
Bistro333 serves fresh market-to-table cuisine for breakfast, lunch and dinner. Guests can grab a drink at Bar 333, which offers cocktails, wines and a variety of beers. A full-service Starbucks® coffee shop is located on site.
The hotel offers 33,000 sq. ft. of business and event space, including a rooftop ballroom with panoramic city views. A full-service business center is also available on-site.
Potawatomi Bingo Casino and Harley Davidson Headquarters are both an 8-minute drive away. General Mitchell International Airport is a 15-minute drive away.

description:

Located in Milwaukee, a 13-minute walk from Marquette University, SpringHill Suites by Marriott Milwaukee Downtown has accommodations with a fitness center and private parking. Popular points of interest near SpringHill Suites by Marriott Milwaukee Downtown include Riverside Theater, Pabst Theater and Milwaukee Theater. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 6.8 miles from the hotel.

Featuring a fitness center, the 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with free WiFi, each with a private bathroom. The hotel provides a hot tub and a 24-hour front desk.

name: The Iron Horse Hotel
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at The Iron Horse Hotel! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Just blocks from the Wisconsin Center, this luxury boutique hotel is a renovated 100-year-old downtown warehouse with sophisticated amenities across the bridge from the Harley-Davidson Museum.
Smyth Restaurant features regional cuisine and an extensive wine bar. Breakfast, brunch, lunch, and dinner are served on various days. BRANDED Bar serves light snacks and signature cocktails, and The Yard features American cuisine and outdoor dining seasonally.
Enjoy amenities such as covered motorcycle parking at The Iron Horse. Guest rooms have custom hooks for hanging heavy leathers and a bench for storing boots and helmets. Guests also have access to the on-site retail shop for travel essentials.

name: Homewood Suites By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown
description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Homewood Suites By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown is located in Milwaukee, 1.1 miles from Marquette University and 3.7 miles from University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee. This 3-star hotel provides a spa experience, with its fitness center and hot tub. Miller Park is 4.4 miles away and Milwaukee Institute of Art and Design is a 8-minute walk from the hotel.
Guest rooms are equipped with air conditioning, a flat-screen TV with cable channels, a fridge, a coffee machine, a shower, free toiletries and a desk. Featuring a private bathroom with a bath and a hairdryer, rooms at the hotel also offer free WiFi. At Homewood Suites By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown each room is equipped with bed linen and towels.
Guests at the accommodation can enjoy a buffet or an American breakfast.
A business center and laundry facilities are available at Homewood Suites By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown. Speaking English and Spanish, staff are ready to help around the clock at the reception.
Popular points of interest near the hotel include Eisner Museum, Riverside Theater and Pabst Theater. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 6.2 miles from Homewood Suites By Hilton Milwaukee Downtown.

name: Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee Downtown
description:
In the heart of downtown Milwaukee, this hotel offers spacious rooms with free Wi-Fi and large flat-screen TVs. A modern fitness center is available on site.
Tea and coffee-making essentials, a refrigerator and a microwave are available in every room and suite at Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee Downtown. An iPod docking station and ironing facilities are also provided in each room.
Guests can enjoy the five story atrium with marble, granite and iron finishes or relax under the immense skylight. A laundromat and a business center are available to all guests.
Great American Grill, on the property, offers dining options for breakfast lunch and dinner. The Pavilion Pantry offers an assortment of beverages and ready-to-cook meals bound for the in-room microwave or refrigerator. Cocktails are served each evening in the Pavilion Lounge.
BMO Harris Bradley Center, Frontier Airlines Center and the Milwaukee Theater are within one mile of this hotel. Discovery World and the shores of Lake Michigan are a 5 minute drive away.

name: Saint Kate - The Arts Hotel
description:
You're eligible for a Genius discount at Saint Kate - The Arts Hotel! To save at this property, all you have to do is sign in.
Located in the heart of Milwaukee's downtown theater district Saint Kate offers panoramic views of the city, fine-dining restaurant options, a 24-hour business center and free
WiFi. The Marcus Performing Arts Center is a 2 minutes' walk away.
Every room at the Saint Kate - The Arts Hotel provides a flat-screen cable TV and a work desk with an ergonomic chair. service is available from  7-11am and 5-10pm.
Saint Kate - The Arts Hotel offers three onsite restaurants and two bars. There is a rotating art exhibit in the lounge area and throughout the hotel
Cathedral Square Park is 4 blocks away from the hotel. Milwaukee Art Museum is a 5-minute drive away. Fiserv Forum is a 9 minutes' walk from the hotel.

name: Brewhouse Inn and Suites
description:
Located inside the old Pabst Blue Ribbon Brewery, this historic Milwaukee hotel is a 12-minute walk away from BMO Harris Bradley Center and offers an outdoor beer garden, complimentary breakfast and free WiFi.
Every room at Brewhouse Inn and Suites features artful décor coupled with modern amenities, including a flat-screen TV with premium cable channels and fully-equipped kitchens with a dining table and chairs.
Jackson’s Blue Ribbon Pub offers classic American bar food for lunch and dinner. For convenience, in-room dining services are available for guests.
Guests can work out at the on-site fitness center or relax on the hotel’s green roof terrace. A business center and guest laundry services are also available.
The Harley-Davidson Museum, Miller Park and the Milwaukee Art Museum are all within 2 miles of the hotel. General Mitchell International Airport is a 15-minute drive away.

description:
Adjacent to the Wisconsin Center, this hotel in Milwaukee, Wisconsin  is near many points of interest and offers a variety of convenient amenities and services.
Doubletree by Hilton Milwaukee Downtown is just steps from the Bradley Center sports and entertainment complex. Guests can also visit the Milwaukee Public Museum, the Milwaukee Art Museum and the Potawatomi Bingo Casino.
Guests can workout in the fitness center at the Milwaukee Doubletree. The on-site Avenue Bar & Grill serves American bistro-style dishes for breakfast, lunch and dinner. For appetizers, local beers and 2 plasma TVs, guests can stop by the hotel's Avenue Bar.

name: Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee Airport
description:
This Milwaukee hotel is less than 1.2 mi from the General Mitchell Airport and offers a free 24-hour shuttle. It also offers a restaurant, indoor pool and rooms with a 32-inch flat-screen TV.
Guest rooms at the Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee are equipped with a microwave and a refrigerator. The spacious rooms are also furnished with a large work desk.
Milwaukee Airport Hilton Garden Inn offers a full-service business center. Guests have free access to the hot tub and gym.
Hilton Garden Inn Milwaukee Airport offers a 24-hour convenience store. The Garden Grille is open all day and drinks are available at the Garden Bar.
Downtown Milwaukee and Discovery World Science Museum are a 15-minute drive from the Hilton Garden Inn. Pabst Mansion is also a 15- minute drive and Miller Park is 20 minutes away.

name: Crowne Plaza Hotel Milwaukee South, an IHG Hotel
description:
Located conveniently off I-94, this Milwaukee accommodations offers rooms with free WiFi and flat-screen TVs. A 24-hour free shuttle service to General Mitchell International Airport is offered to all guests.
Tea and coffee-making facilities are available in each air-conditioned room at Crowne Plaza Hotel Milwaukee South.  A TV with premium cable channels is also featured in all rooms.
Guests of Crowne Plaza Hotel Milwaukee South can enjoy a swim in the indoor swimming pool or relax in the on-site hot tub. A business center with fax and photocopying facilities and a fitness center are available 24-hours a day.
Altitude Restaurant and Lounge, located within the hotel, offers American contemporary cuisine with daily food and drink specials. There is also a Starbucks Cafe onsite that is open 7 days a week.
Central Milwaukee is located less than a 20 minutes’ drive from this hotel. The Milwaukee Art Museum is 10 miles away.

name: Econo Lodge Milwaukee Airport
description:
Conveniently located 1 mi from General Mitchell International Airport, this Milwaukee, Wisconsin hotel provides free airport transport for guests during select hours. Free WiFi and free parking are included.
Econo Lodge is just minutes from the Miller Brewing Company Milwaukee Brewery and the shores of Lake Michigan. Public transport and the Park-and-Ride car park for Summerfest, one of the world's largest music festivals, are within walking distance of the hotel. Several restaurants and shops are also nearby.
After a restful night's sleep wake up with Econo Lodge's complimentary deluxe breakfast. Guests will also appreciate amenities such as complimentary wireless high-speed internet access, complimentary local calls and business services. Guests can leave their car parked at the hotel while they travel (charges apply).

name: Hawthorn Suites By Wyndham Oak Creek/Milwaukee Airport
description:
Stay longer for less at the Hawthorne Suites Milwaukee Airport hotel, conveniently located off Interstate 94 and minutes from the General Mitchell International Airport. This Oak Creek, WI extended stay hotel is also close to the Bradley Center arena, Milwaukee Area Technical College (MATC) Oak Creek campus, the Milwaukee County Zoo and the Mitchell Park Horticultural Conservatory.
Scenically located on the shores of Lake Michigan in downtown Milwaukee, the Summerfest music festival grounds are 10 miles from our hotel. Additional nearby points of interest within 15 miles include Miller Park baseball stadium, Miller Brewing Company Milwaukee Brewery, Marquette University and the University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee.
You will feel right at home at Hawthorne Suites Milwaukee Airport; they offer an array of amenities including fully equipped kitchens in all rooms, weekly housekeeping services, free continental breakfast, free premium cable television with movie channels and free wireless high-speed Internet access.  For added convenience, they also provide free local calls, an exercise room and guest laundry facilities.
Business travelers can appreciate conveniences in every suite like two-line speakerphones, voice mail, spacious work areas with ergonomic office chairs and access to copy and fax services.
The all-suite hotel features one- and two-bedroom suites providing separate areas for relaxing, sleeping and eating. All rooms are designed with the extended stay traveler in mind, and are furnished with fully equipped kitchens that include a refrigerator, freezer, microwave, coffee maker, cookware, utensils and dishwasher. All suites also feature full-size sofa sleepers, irons and ironing boards.

userReviews.title: Best Budget Option in the MKE Airport Area
userReviews.positive: Awesome amenities. Great pool, jacuzzi and pool side area. The beds are comfortable and the blankets are thick. Hot breakfast with eggs, bacon, sausage and waffles amongst other grab and go options. Staff was super nice and helpful as my 87 year old grandmother locked herself out of the room when I was not there and the staff let her back in without a hassle even though her name was not on the room. Very nice people.Very accommodating. Our room was handicap accessible and had a shower chair in the closet. Super bonus if traveling with older family members. One of the better options in the area. Location was across the street from a great Mexican Restaurant with an awesome bar area. The hotel bar was also very nice and the staff treated my grandmother like a VIP. I will definitely be staying here again on my next trip to Milwaukee.

name: Holiday Inn Milwaukee Airport, an IHG Hotel
description:
Located less than 2 miles from General Mitchell International Airport, this Holiday Inn offers free airport shuttle service as well as an indoor pool and hot tub.
Free WiFi service and cable TV is featured in all rooms at the Milwaukee Airport Holiday Inn. Some rooms include private kitchenettes and whirlpool spas.
The Holiday Inn Hotel & Suites also offers a fitness center and a lobby with a fireplace.
Dining is available on-site at the M.K.E. Bar and Grille, featuring traditional American burgers, steak and fish dishes. A 24-hour convenience store is also available at the hotel.
The Miller Brewing Company, which offers free tours of its facility, and the Potawatomi Bingo Casino are each a 15-minute drive from the Holiday Inn Milwaukee Airport. The Milwaukee County Zoo is less than 13 miles away.

address.full: 545 West Layton Avenue, Milwaukee, WI 53207, United States of America

name: Super 8 by Wyndham Milwaukee Airport
description:
Offering 24-hour complimentary airport shuttle service, this Milwaukee, Wisconsin hotel is just 3 minutes’ drive from General Mitchell International Airport. Free Wi-Fi access is available.
A flat-screen cable TV, work desk and air conditioning are included in each room at Super 8 Milwaukee Airport. Rooms also feature a microwave, refrigerator and coffeemaker. Private bathrooms are equipped with a hairdryer.
Super 8 Milwaukee Airport provides free airport shuttle service and a 24-hour front desk. Meeting facilities and a shared lounge are also available. Overnight guests can access free on-site parking. Long-term parking is available for a surcharge.
A daily complimentary grab and go breakfast is offered on site. Brass Monkey Milwaukee Pub & Grill is 2 minutes’ drive.
The Milwaukee Airport Super 8 is 8 mi from Milwaukee city center. The Harley-Davison Museum is 6.5 mi away.

address.full: 5253 South Howell Avenue, Milwaukee, WI 53207, United States of America

description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Red Lotus Inn is located in Milwaukee, 6.1 miles from Miller Park and 7.1 miles from Marquette University. The 3-star hotel has air-conditioned rooms with a private bathroom and free WiFi. Private parking is available on site.
The rooms in the hotel are equipped with a flat-screen TV with cable channels. At Red Lotus Inn rooms contain bed linen and towels.
Speaking English, Spanish, Gujarati and Hindi at the reception, staff will be happy to provide guests with practical advice on the area.
University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee is 11 miles from the accommodation, while Pitman Theater is 2.3 miles from the property. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 3.1 miles from Red Lotus Inn.

userReviews.title: budget hotel under new ownership with a good attitude
userReviews.positive:
The hotel is still being remodelled, but I didn’t notice any disturbances and everything worked. Needs a few finishing touches, but that’s alright.
I liked how they’re doing things a bit differently. The décor may not be one I would have chosen, but it does provide some very welcome relief from the usual stuff I know from the big chains.
This being a budget hotel, I did enjoy that money was spent on small things that make a difference.
For instance, the common question “How much would it have cost them to put a towel rack and a few hooks on the bathroom walls?” did not need asking.
The small selection of the usual toiletries may have had Rupee signs on it, but it was name-brand.
There was no bathtub, but the shower was spacious with a good water supply and (again) decent storage for your shampoo bottles and the like.
All in all, I wish this business a lot of success. You’re on a good way, so please keep going.

userReviews.negative: I should not have checked in when I arrive at 11:00 pm. I relied on Booking.com ratings and that was also a mistake. This is an old facility with only a fresh coat of paint about 2 miles from the airport in what I thought was a safe part of town. The motel was set back from the street, with poor lighting in the parking area and very few cars. The person checking me in can best described as sleezy. Because I had to catch a very early flight, I got up at 4:00am. At 4:45 am when I started my rental SUV to leave for the airport, I found out that the catalytic converter had been stolen from the vehicle. Although I have no way of knowing, my intuition tells me that the motel was somehow involved with the theft because my rental was parked very close to the motel entrance. Now I have to pay a $500 insurance deductible for the replacement of the catalytic converter. It was an expensive stay. DO NOT STAY AT THIS MOTEL. And don't trust Booking.com's ratings.

A fitness center with cardio equipment and free weights is available to all guests of Milwaukee Airport Courtyard. The 24 hour front desk offers guests fax and photocopying facilities.
The Bistro and Lounge, in the hotel lobby, offers dining options for breakfast and dinner in a casual atmosphere.
Downtown Milwaukee is 7 miles from the property. Marquette University, Miller Park and the Milwaukee Art Museum are within a 15 minute drive of this hotel.

name: Sleep Inn & Suites Airport Milwaukee
description:
The Sleep Inn & Suites Airport hotel is less than two miles from General Mitchell International Airport and offers a Stay & Fly package. Downtown Milwaukee, the Bradley Center, Harley-Davidson Museum and Miller Park baseball field are minutes from this Milwaukee, WI hotel. Enjoy the annual Summerfest, the "World's Largest Music Festival," located just eight miles away.
Nearby Milwaukee Theater District offers a variety of entertainment venues where you can see the latest plays, musicals, concerts and more. Several Wisconsin specialty stores, retailers, restaurants and cocktail lounges can be found in the surrounding area. Additional attractions include Marquette University, Miller Brewing Company Milwaukee Brewery, Milwaukee Mile racetrack, Discovery World museum and Frontier Airlines Center.
This Milwaukee, WI hotel offers full-service features and amenities like free airport transportation, free Morning Medley Hot Breakfast, free coffee, free wireless high-speed Internet access and free USA Today. After a busy day of meetings or an exciting day of sightseeing, guests are invited to relax by the indoor heated pool and hot tub. We also have an exercise room for you to enjoy.
Business travelers can appreciate conveniences like a public computer with Internet access and copy and fax services. The banquet room can accommodate up to 35 people for most business or social functions. For added convenience, guest laundry facilities are located on the premises. Free parking is available and can accommodate most cars, trucks or buses.
All guest rooms at this smoke-free hotel have microwaves, refrigerators, flat-screen televisions, coffee makers, spacious work desks, hair dryers, irons, ironing boards and cable television. Some rooms have curved shower rods and sofa sleepers.

userReviews.positive:
We really enjoyed our stay here. perfect location close to downtown Milwaukee. The staff was very friendly and welcoming. Everyone we seen always had a smile and always said have a nice or great day. We didn’t have any problems when we had asked for extra bath towels (usually we have run into we cannot have extra towels no rhyme or reason just told no). But we only experienced the best service from check-in to check-out. 
The pool and hot tub were very clean. There were plenty of towels for guests. The pool towels are pretty big, so they dry you off really well. We didn’t use the workout room but it was very clean. 
More importantly the rooms were very clean. The bathroom was also very clean and a nice size. 
The coffee is available 24 hours and very good Always fresh when we got a cup. 
We will definitely stay here again on our next trip.
userReviews.negative: The only complaint we had was breakfast. We tried a few of the options and nothing tasted good. The sausage had a weird taste to me. Almost like it was microwaved. I had a bowl of cereal but couldn’t have more than a spoonful due to the milk tasting like metal. It was not expired milk - not even close to expiration date. It just had a metal taste to it. Lastly I tried a bagel with peanut butter I had only half of it. I felt bad since I threw away so much food, but it did not taste good to me. There are several options but nothing was to my liking.

name: Best Western Plus Milwaukee West
description:
Less than 5 miles from Milwaukee city center and 3 minutes’ drive from Miller Park, this hotel features a heated indoor pool on site. Free Wi-Fi and a flat-screen TV are provided in every guest room.
Tea and coffee-making facilities are offered in all rooms at Best Western Plus Milwaukee West. Each room also comes equipped with a work desk and a hairdryer.
Guests can enjoy a workout in the fitness center of relax in the hot tub at Best Western Plus Milwaukee West. A business center is also available on site.
The Wisconsin State Fair Park and Expo Center and the Milwaukee County Zoo are 10 minutes’ drive from this hotel. The shores of Lake Michigan, Summerfest and the Milwaukee Art Museum are within 6 miles.

name: Quality Suites Milwaukee Airport
description:
Less than 3 miles away from General Mitchel International Airport and Milwaukee Airport, this hotel is located in Milwaukee and offers free airport shuttle services, complimentary breakfast and free WiFi.
Every smoke-free room at Quality Suites Milwaukee Airport provides a living room with a sofa bed and a flat-screen cable TV. A microwave, refrigerator and coffee maker are also included.
Guests can swim in the indoor pool and hot tub, work out at the on-site fitness center or play arcade video games in the hotel game room. Guest laundry services and free parking are also offered.
Marquette University and Miller Park are both 6 miles away from the hotel. Milwaukee County Zoo is a 20-minute drive away.

name: Knickerbocker on the Lake
description:
Featuring a full kitchen in every room, this downtown Milwaukee hotel is a 4-minute walk from the Lake Michigan waterfront. Free Wi-Fi access is available.
Cable TV is provided in every spacious room at Knickerbocker on the Lake. Featuring a bathtub or shower, the private bathrooms also include a hairdryer.
The Knick Salon and Spa features massage services, hair and skin care, and much more.  Other facilities include meeting facilities and dry cleaning.
The Knick Restaurant is on site and serves American cuisine in an upscale atmosphere. Guests can enjoy their meal on the outdoor patio that overlooks Lake Michigan.
The hotel is 1 miles from Midwest Airlines Center, 4 miles from Miller Park and about a half mile from Milwaukee Art Museum. General Mitchell Airport is 7 miles away.

name: Rodeway Inn & Suites Milwaukee Airport
description:
Just three miles from the General Mitchell International Airport, the Rodeway Inn & Suites hotel provides free airport transportation for its guests. Local points of interest like Miller Park (home of the Milwaukee Brewers), the Milwaukee County Zoo, the Discovery World museum and Marquette University are all close to this Milwaukee, WI hotel.
Wisconsin offers many things to see and do. Visitors can enjoy the nearby Harley-Davidson Museum that features a large collection of motorcycles and memorabilia. This facility also offers plant tours where you can get an up-close look at how these legendary choppers are made, and features a number of specialty stores, interactive exhibits, cafes and more.
Downtown Milwaukee, famous for its world-class breweries, is minutes away. Local businesses like the Miller Brewing Company Milwaukee Brewery and Lakefront Brewery have tours throughout the year. Countless entertainment venues, shopping centers and restaurants are close by.
Guests of this Milwaukee, WI hotel can enjoy features and amenities, free wireless high-speed Internet access, free parking. This Wisconsin hotel offers business travelers access to modern conveniences like copy and fax service.
In addition to standard amenities, all of our guest rooms are equipped with refrigerators, microwaves, curved shower rods, hair dryers, irons, ironing boards and cable television. Select rooms also have whirlpool bathtubs, hot tubs and work desks. Handicap accessible and nonsmoking rooms can be requested.
For added convenience, this is a pet-friendly hotel (fees apply) and coin-operated laundry facilities are located on the premises.

name: Holiday Inn Express & Suites Milwaukee NW - Park Place, an IHG Hotel
description:
Holiday Inn Express & Suites Milwaukee NW - Park Place, an IHG Hotel is located just six miles from the Milwaukee County Zoo. This Milwaukee, WI hotel is minutes from popular attractions like Marquette University, the Bradley Center indoor arena, the Midwest Airlines Center convention and exhibition facility and Miller Park, home of the Milwaukee Brewers baseball team.
Visitors can enjoy a boat cruise in the scenic Milwaukee Harbor. Stroll along the Milwaukee RiverWalk, which connects the city's many waterfront neighborhoods. A variety of riverside bistros, cafés, coffee shops, entertainment options and restaurants line the streets of Milwaukee. You'll enjoy browsing and shopping at the number of hip art galleries and chic specialty boutiques around the city.
Guests of this Milwaukee, WI hotel can enjoy amenities and features like free wireless high-speed Internet access, free local calls and it is a pet-friendly hotel; fees apply.
After an exciting day of city life, relax in the indoor heated pool. Be sure to take advantage of the exercise room. Two meeting rooms are available to accommodate most events and business functions. Access to copy and fax services is offered.
All guest rooms come equipped with refrigerators, microwaves, coffee makers, curved shower rods, desks, hair dryers, irons, ironing boards, voice mail, sofa sleepers and cable television. Keep your electronic devices charged with the recharge device including AC and USB outlets provided in all guest rooms. Two-room suites are offered. Laundry facilities are located on the premises for added guest convenience and we have ample parking that can accommodate most cars, trucks or busses.

userReviews.title: Amtrak cross-country trip -- 1-night stay
userReviews.positive:
We were taking a winter cross-country Amtrak trip  and stopped in Milwaukee for a night. We booked a queen room at The Plaza Hotel but they upgraded us to a king suite-- a nice surprise! They also let us check in early to accommodate our early afternoon train arrival. 
It turned out there was a problem with the heat in the first room, so they switched us to a different king suite, and they also gave us an extra blanket and space heater. It was a short trip but a very comfortable place to stay. 
Location-wise, it's not right in the middle of things, but if you like walking, you can walk a bit and get to the major nearby sites. Pretty close to the museum/Calatrava "wings" addition, which was one thing we definitely wanted to see; and we also walked to the Riverwalk/historic 3rd Ward.
I appreciated that the onsite restaurant/cafe (open for breakfast/lunch) had gluten-free veggie options, including GF bread! Conveniently, there was also a grocery store,/pharmacy behind the hotel.
All in all, a lovely stay!
userReviews.negative: Walking through the crowded cafe dining room with our luggage to get to the stairs/hallway to get to our room. (The hotel discloses that there's no elevator--and  there are accommodations for those who can't walk up stairs-- it's just unfortunate that because it's an old building, the path for some guests goes through the dining room.)

name: Norwood Inn & Suites Milwaukee
description:
Featuring 3-star accommodations, Norwood Inn & Suites Milwaukee is located in Milwaukee, 10 miles from Miller Park and 10 miles from University of Wisconsin-Milwaukee. This 3-star hotel offers room service, a 24-hour front desk and free WiFi. Wisconsin State Fair Park is 8.7 miles away and Milwaukee Mile Race Track is 8.9 miles from the hotel.
At the hotel, each room is equipped with a desk, a TV, a private bathroom, bed linen and towels. Guest rooms will provide guests with a fridge.
A continental breakfast is available daily at Norwood Inn & Suites Milwaukee.
Marquette University is 13 miles from the accommodation, while Milwaukee Mile is 8.5 miles away. The nearest airport is Milwaukee Mitchell International Airport, 19 miles from Norwood Inn & Suites Milwaukee.
